ANC secretary general, Ace Magashule, speaks to eNCA Political Editor, Vuyo Mvoko, about the NEC's latest meeting. JOHANNESBURG - If you're unhappy with how President Cyril Ramaphosa and his Cabinet ministers are handling the electricity crisis, don't single them out for criticism. The entire ANC leadership should take the blame. READ: Eskom not expecting load-shedding this weekend Well, that's the word from party secretary general, Ace Magashule. He says the ANC national executive has satisfied itself that not only has the president and his executive consulted widely, but that everything they are doing is in line with ANC thinking and policies. Magashule was speaking to eNCA political editor, Vuyo Mvoko earlier this week, about the NEC's latest meeting. Watch the interview in the video above